Summary: Large starlike orb, bright orange/yellow in color, slowly moving N to SW
trends: There have been 4 other sightings in Shenandoah
There were no other sightings in Shenandoah on or around November 14th 2012
divs: sighting detailsat approximately 7:15 p.m., november 14, i stepped outside our back door to see what the weather was like. i started to return inside when i noticed a large star-like, bright orange\yellow "orb" traveling n to sw. observation only lasted about 5 seconds. it went behind a tree but i could see it as it passed between the bare branches. then all of a sudden it disappeared, just as if a light switch was turned off. i kept watching but it never reappeared. there was no sound.
